    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Compound vaults in which intersecting barrel vaults are of differing widths, the ridges of the same height but the springing lines of different height, producing a groin line of double curvature. Compound vaults in which intersecting barrel vaults are of differing widths, the ridges of the same height but the springing lines of different height, producing a groin line of double curvature.</Note_Text>
